[Leishmaniasis in Central America including Honduras is has a zoonotic
reservoir and is transmitted to humans by sandflies. There are no recent
data on the number of cases in Honduras. A newsletter from the Pan American
Health Organization PAHO
(http://www.paho.org/english/ad/dpc/cd/leishmaniasis.htm) was updated in
2007 but contains no country specific data.

HealthMap location: http://healthmap.org/r/11dt. - Mod.EP]
